Dasypus bellus, the beautiful armadillo, is an extinct armadillo species endemic to North America and South America from the Pleistocene, living from 1.8 myaâ€”11,000 years ago, existing for approximately 1.789 million years.Slightly larger than its living relative, the nine-banded armadillo, its fossils are known from Florida and records extend west to New Mexico and north to Iowa and Indiana.